SIMPLE: inhabitant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inhabitant
<hw>In*hab"it*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inhabitans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>inhabitare</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who dwells or resides permanently in a place, as
distinguished from a transient lodger or visitor; <as>as, an
<ex>inhabitant</ex> of a house, a town, a city, county, or
state</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Frail <xex>inhabitants</xex> of earth.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In this place, they report that they saw <qex>inhabitants</qex>
which were very fair and fat people.</q> <rj><qau>Abp.
Abbot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who has a legal settlement in a
town, city, or parish; a permanent resident.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inhabitate</ent>⟦br⟧
